HEADWORD: Restiform
<hw>Res"ti*form</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧s"t⟦icr⟧*f⟦ocir⟧rm)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos><ety>[L. <ets>restis</ets> rope + <ets>-form</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Formed like a rope; -- applied especially to
several ropelike bundles or masses of fibers on the dorsal side of the
medulla oblongata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

